19. What are dangling images?
A: Dangling images are Docker images that are not tagged and are not referenced by any container. They are typically created during the build process when intermediate layers are generated but not used in the final image. These images can take up disk space and can be safely removed if they are no longer needed. 
You can identify dangling images using the following command:

    docker images -f "dangling=true"

